    • Method Detail

      • p$p

        TreeInterface p$p​(Kleisli<Person,​Person> k)
        This Interface is implemented for Monadic Navigation; x$y functions are analogs of bind (>>=) operator from Haskell. x_y functions are analogs of forgetful bind (>>) from Haskell. Inside Tree we have 2 lists, hence we have 4 implementations of each bind. Perhaps it would be better to call it Diadic navigation. arguments should have signature :: x -> [y]
        Parameters:
        k - :: x -> [y];
        Returns:
        TreeInterface;
